  "text": "The HotSpot JIT compilation pipeline is built on a hierarchical architecture. CompileBroker (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compileBroker.hpp) is the central broker managing all compilation requests across the JVM. CompilerThread (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compilerThread.hpp) is the JavaThread subclass that executes compilation tasks. AbstractCompiler (src/hotspot/share/compiler/abstractCompiler.hpp) is the base class providing the common interface for all JIT compilers. The two primary JIT implementations inherit from AbstractCompiler: the C1 compiler (src/hotspot/share/c1/c1_Compiler.hpp) is the first-tier JIT focused on fast compilation with basic optimizations, while the C2 compiler (src/hotspot/share/opto/c2compiler.hpp) is the optimizing JIT tier that performs aggressive optimizations on hot code paths. This two-tier compilation strategy allows the JVM to balance startup performance with long-running performance."
}

